{{Politics of Lebanon}} This is a '''list of [[Presidents]] (and acting [[Presidents]]) of [[Lebanon]]''' since the creation of the office in 1926. Though it is not specifically stated in the constitution, an unwritten understanding known as the [[National Pact]], agreed in 1943, has resulted in the holder of the post being a [[Maronite Christian]] in every electoral cycle since that time. This agreement had to be suspended twice, when two [[Muslims]], the former [[Prime Minister of Lebanon|Prime Minister]]s had to step in as acting presidents, [[Selim Hoss]] in 1988 and [[Fuad Siniora]] in 2007.
